Facts on the infections of sexual transmission
Which are the main sexually transmitted diseases?
Among the ETS of bacterial origin are the syphilis, the chlamydia and the gonorrhea.
The ETS of viral origin most usual are Aids, the virus of the papilloma human being, the genital herpes or the hepatitis.
The crab lice and the scabies are among the ETS transmitted by parasites.
